name: Colony Cottage Recreation Center
directions: After entering the building, turn left.  On one side, the right side of the area that you have entered, there is a women's restroom and drinking fountains.  On the opposite side, to your left, is a men's bathroom, drinking fountains, and another separate single-stall bathroom in the corner marked "Family."  You have to go to the "Men's" side to be able to see the "Family" restroom; there isn't one on the "Women's" side.
comment: The Villages Recreation Centers are for The Villages residents and their guests.  While The Villages looks like a gated community, all of its streets are actually public.  You have to enter through gates at guardhouses, but the guards will allow everyone in the "Visitors" lane to enter, without asking for any IDs.  They will just wave you through and open the gate.  While the use of the meeting rooms in the recreation center require a resident ID or guest pass, I doubt that anyone would ask if you just went in to use the restroom.
